Head yellow with vertex, antennae insertion and inferior part of ocular canthus black. Labrum partly brownish. Surface matt with quite deeply impressed punctures, more concentrates on clypeus and ocular rim, slightly smaller on vertex. Frons with a quite long, well definite, narrow longitudinal groove. Antennae (
Fig. 15n
) black, only tips of first four antennomeres somewhat lighter. Antennomeres remarkably lengthened, so that antennae slightly exceed the total body length.
